#Stock transaction program
#Last month, Joe purchased some stock in Acme Software, Inc.
#Details of the purchase:
#-The number of shares that joe purchased was 2000.
#-When Joe purchased the stock, he paid $40000 per share
#-Joe paid his stockbroker a commission that amounted to 3% of the amount he paid
#for the stock.

#Two weeks later, Joe sold the stock. Here are the details of the sale:
#-The number of shares that Joe sold was 2000
#-He sold the stock for $42.75 per share
#-He paid his stockbroker another commission that amounted to 3 percent of
#of the amount he recieved for the stock

#Write a program that displays the following information:
#-The amount of money Joe paid for the stock
#-The amount of commission Joe paid the broker  when he bought the stock
#-The amount for which Jose sold the stock
#-The amount of commission Joe paid his broker when he sold the stock
#Display the amount of money that Joe had left when he sold the stock
#and paid his broker (both times). If this amount if positive, Then
#Joe made a profit, If negative, then Joe lost money.

total_price_stock1 = 2000 * 40000

comm1_perc = (total_price_stock1 * 3)/100

total1 = total_price_stock1 - comm1_perc

#Two weeks later

total_price_stock2 = 2000 * 42.75

comm2_perc = (total_price_stock2 * 3)/100

total2 = total_price_stock2 - comm2_perc

left = total2 - total1

print("The amount paid for the stock: ",total_price_stock1)
print("The comission for the broker: ",comm1_perc)
print("Stock selling price: ",total_price_stock2)
print("Selling commission for the broker: ",comm2_perc)
print("Total buying price: ",total1)
print("Total selling price: ",total2)
print("Joe has lost money: ",left)
